10:03.719 --> 10:06.855
Miguel! Miguel!

10:07.004 --> 10:08.689
What the hell happened?

10:08.695 --> 10:10.481
Once Everado fled, the rival cartels

10:10.487 --> 10:12.321
took out the rest of his crew.

10:12.327 --> 10:14.295
That's the last we heard of him.

10:14.363 --> 10:16.150
And what happened to his family?

10:16.156 --> 10:18.766
They fled to Europe,
living off a nice nest egg

10:18.772 --> 10:20.005
Sanchez left for them.

10:20.011 --> 10:21.678
Wife died a few years back.

10:21.870 --> 10:24.705
Last I heard, his daughter
Soledad was living in Italy.

10:24.773 --> 10:26.371
Exact address is unknown.

10:26.377 --> 10:28.537
She kept a low profile
from rival cartels.

10:28.543 --> 10:30.311
It looks like Carlo Velardi

10:30.317 --> 10:32.742
used to do business with
Sanchez back in the '80s.

10:32.748 --> 10:34.438
Wouldn't be surprised if that's

10:34.444 --> 10:36.188
why Soledad ended up in Italy.

10:36.251 --> 10:39.720
Carlo was offering her
protection, which means

10:39.788 --> 10:41.288
he might know where she is.

10:41.356 --> 10:42.657
Worth a shot.

10:42.663 --> 10:44.742
He said he owed us for helping
catch his son's killer.

10:44.748 --> 10:47.302
Calling in favors from
convicted mobsters

10:47.308 --> 10:49.688
is where I get off the train,

10:49.694 --> 10:51.516
but you kids knock yourselves out.

10:51.522 --> 10:52.789
Thanks, Harper.

10:52.795 --> 10:56.837
Oh, and try not to leave too
much destruction in your wake.

11:01.178 --> 11:03.112
Gwen? Hi.

11:03.118 --> 11:05.452
Does the name Zara Farouk ring a bell?

11:05.458 --> 11:07.252
Besides the obvious part,

11:07.258 --> 11:10.124
- about her last name?
- No, never heard it. Why?

11:10.130 --> 11:12.856
Fabi was looking into a money
trail from a shell company

11:12.862 --> 11:14.396
to somebody by that name.

11:14.402 --> 11:16.563
I called the bank listed
on the transactions,

11:16.569 --> 11:18.437
but they wouldn't give
out any information,

11:18.443 --> 11:21.045
and I can't get a warrant
because the documents

11:21.051 --> 11:22.503
were procured illegally.

11:22.509 --> 11:24.443
Were they ever.

11:24.449 --> 11:26.501
I stole them, and then you did,

11:26.507 --> 11:28.816
which is, like, doubly illegal.

11:28.822 --> 11:30.292
Yes, thank you.

11:30.298 --> 11:33.367
Gwen, I just knew we
could be friends one day.

11:33.373 --> 11:34.866
Okay, I'm hanging up now.

11:34.872 --> 11:36.508
Let us know if you find anything.

11:36.514 --> 11:38.014
All right.

12:22.735 --> 12:25.602
_

12:35.007 --> 12:36.968
Look at McNamara.

12:36.974 --> 12:39.842
He doesn't even know
how to wear a shirt.

12:39.910 --> 12:42.044
Did you hear what happened to his dad?

12:42.050 --> 12:43.289
He's in jail.

12:55.459 --> 12:58.433
Yeah. I hate these things, too, huh?

13:00.427 --> 13:02.328
H-Hey...

13:02.733 --> 13:05.034
Don't let your suit define you.

13:05.102 --> 13:08.104
Okay? Not tonight. Not ever.

13:09.506 --> 13:12.903
Yeah. The Romans said
the clothes make the man.

13:15.705 --> 13:18.080
Um, and how did that work out for them?

13:20.884 --> 13:22.985
See you around, kid.

13:24.360 --> 13:26.689
The proceeds from tonight's auction

13:26.757 --> 13:29.692
go towards scholarships
for those students who have

13:29.760 --> 13:33.262
demonstrated exceptional
academic achievement.

13:33.268 --> 13:35.794
And while those students
have earned their place here,

13:35.800 --> 13:38.468
it would only be fair to say
that none of us would be here

13:38.474 --> 13:41.558
if not for the generosity of our host,

13:41.564 --> 13:43.458
the man who donated

13:43.464 --> 13:46.533
this incredible array of auction items

13:46.743 --> 13:48.811
from his own private collection.

13:48.879 --> 13:52.515
Ladies and gentlemen, Mr. Jacob Reece.

14:08.641 --> 14:11.422
_

14:54.344 --> 14:57.513
Carlo Velardi says it's this way.

15:29.513 --> 15:31.514
Señora Soledad.

15:33.216 --> 15:35.418
I was told you have some information

15:35.424 --> 15:37.270
about my father's whereabouts.

15:37.276 --> 15:39.768
Carlo assured me you
wouldn't waste my time.

15:39.963 --> 15:42.291
We're here to prevent a terrorist group

15:42.297 --> 15:44.161
from carrying out a deadly attack.

15:44.229 --> 15:45.928
But to do that, we need to find out

15:45.934 --> 15:47.384
what happened to your father.

15:47.390 --> 15:49.799
With your help, we think we can.

15:50.901 --> 15:52.301
You have five minutes.

15:53.087 --> 15:56.572
We have the last known
recording of your father,

15:56.578 --> 15:58.497
courtesy of the DEA.

16:00.108 --> 16:02.640
_

16:07.614 --> 16:08.947
Sí.

16:10.153 --> 16:13.022
This man says that he is with you.

16:13.028 --> 16:14.459
Shaw?

16:14.465 --> 16:16.396
- Oh, God.
- What the hell are you doing here?

16:16.402 --> 16:18.522
I could ask you two the same damn thing.

16:18.528 --> 16:21.400
That doesn't make sense.
You followed us.

16:21.406 --> 16:22.539
So he is with you?

16:22.545 --> 16:23.648
- Yes.
- No.

16:23.654 --> 16:25.168
- We are done here.
- Oh, hold up...

16:25.174 --> 16:27.436
Whoa, whoa, wait, wait, wait.
We know him.

16:27.442 --> 16:29.576
He just didn't come with us.

16:29.932 --> 16:31.333
Espera.

16:32.152 --> 16:33.709
And whose fault is that?

16:33.715 --> 16:36.784
You two found Antony and didn't
even bother to reach out?

16:36.790 --> 16:38.055
Antony?

16:38.316 --> 16:40.068
As in Antony and Cleopatra?

16:40.074 --> 16:42.351
- Yeah.
- Yes. That's why we're here.

16:42.419 --> 16:44.954
The terrorists we're after
are looking for Cleopatra.

16:45.021 --> 16:46.956
Now, if we can find her before they do,

16:46.962 --> 16:48.547
we can stop their attack.

16:48.553 --> 16:49.976
We have reason to suspect your

16:49.982 --> 16:51.589
father was in possession of her.

16:51.595 --> 16:53.028
He was.

16:53.096 --> 16:55.798
He was... I remember
seeing a golden coffin.

16:55.804 --> 17:00.474
Soledad, can you, can you help
us figure out where he went?

17:01.598 --> 17:04.540
You said, uh, that you had a recording?

